Your initMap function looks good! The only thing missing is the addSampleZones function that creates the sample data. You need to add this function to your App object.

Find where your App object is defined (around line 3300-3400) and add this function right after initMap:

```javascript
initMap: function() {
    // ... your existing initMap code ...
},

// ADD THIS NEW FUNCTION RIGHT HERE:
addSampleZones: function(mapData) {
    console.log('Adding sample zones');
    const center = mapData.center || [-33.7, 150.3];
    
    // Create sample zones
    mapData.zones = [
        {
            name: 'Zone 1 - Native Forest',
            coords: [
                [center[0] - 0.02, center[1] - 0.02],
                [center[0] - 0.02, center[1] + 0.02],
                [center[0] + 0.02, center[1] + 0.02],
                [center[0] + 0.02, center[1] - 0.02]
            ],
            color: '#3498db'
        },
        {
            name: 'Zone 2 - Wetland Area',
            coords: [
                [center[0] + 0.03, center[1] - 0.03],
                [center[0] + 0.03, center[1] + 0.01],
                [center[0] + 0.07, center[1] + 0.01],
                [center[0] + 0.07, center[1] - 0.03]
            ],
            color: '#27ae60'
        }
    ];
    
    // Create sample vegetation markers
    mapData.vegetationMarkers = [
        { name: 'Eucalyptus pauciflora (Snow Gum)', coords: [center[0] - 0.01, center[1] + 0.01] },
        { name: 'Acacia melanoxylon (Blackwood)', coords: [center[0] + 0.01, center[1] - 0.01] }
    ];
    
    // Create sample weed markers
    mapData.weedMarkers = [
        { name: 'Rubus fruticosus (Blackberry)', coords: [center[0] + 0.02, center[1] + 0.02] }
    ];
    
    // Save the data
    Utils.saveData();
    console.log('Sample zones added:', mapData.zones.length);
},

updateMapForCurrentSite: function() {
    this.initMap();
},
// ... rest of your functions continue
```

This function is called from your initMap here:

```javascript
// Add sample zones if none exist
if (!mapData.zones || mapData.zones.length === 0) {
    this.addSampleZones(mapData);  // <-- This calls the function
}
```

Without this function, when there are no zones in mapData.zones, nothing gets created. The addSampleZones function populates mapData.zones, mapData.vegetationMarkers, and mapData.weedMarkers with sample data, which then gets drawn on the map by the code you already have.

After adding this function, your map should show:

· Blue polygon for Zone 1
· Green polygon for Zone 2
· Green dots for vegetation markers
· Red dots for weed markers
